The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports
Archives
 ICC meeting in Dubai from today
A STAFF REPORTERCalcutta: Three directors will be attending for the first time when the ICC Board meets in Dubai on Tuesday and Wednesday, according to a media release. They are Major General Sina Ibn Jamali, the newly appointed president of the Bangladesh Cricket Board, the England and Wales Cricket Boards new chairman Giles Clarke, and Dr Julian Hunte, president of the West Indies Cricket Board. The agenda for the meeting includes:  The Board will consider recommendations made by the Umpires Task Force, which met in September, concerning the structure, support mechanisms, remuneration and selection of officials in the future.  The ICCs centenary is in 2009 and the Board will consider appropriate ways to mark the occasion.  With the current CEO, Malcolm Speed, set to step down at next years ICC Annual Conference in June/July, the Board will be asked to appoint recruitment consultants to help fill the position. It will also establish its own recruitment committee, which will make a recommendation to the next Board meeting, in March 2008.  Approval of terms of reference for a Permanent Medical Committee. 
